      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Offered is a mechanically sound E92 M3 featuring the high-revving S65 4.0L naturally aspirated V8. This power unit utilizes eight individual throttle bodies and a 12.0:1 compression ratio to deliver a linear power band up to an 8,400 RPM redline. Power is sent through a 6-speed longitudinal manual gearbox to the rear wheels via the M Variable Differential Lock, which provides proactive torque vectoring. The chassis benefits from a factory carbon fiber roof panel, lowering the center of gravity for improved roll gradient. This example features functional Electronic Damper Control (EDC) and has undergone comprehensive preventative maintenance, including rod bearing replacement and updated throttle actuators. The suspension bushings remain stiff, and the hydraulic steering rack offers the precise feedback characteristic of the E9X platform.",
